Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:03.27,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}土星上的胜利
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.27,0:00:08.27,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}视频、英文字幕版权：NASA JPL\N渣翻中字/时间轴：PolestarX
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.27,0:00:12.51,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}如果让人描绘一幅代表行星的图画，\N{\fs13}Ask someone to draw a picture of a planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.54,0:00:14.68,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}结果很可能就是这个：\N{\fs13}and odds are it will be this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.78,0:00:19.55,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}太阳系中的第六颗行星，\N{\fs13}It is the sixth planet out from the sun
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.58,0:00:22.22,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}也是第二大的行星\N{\fs13}and the second-largest in our solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.59,0:00:26.22,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这 就是土星\N{\fs13}It is, of course, Saturn,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.25,0:00:29.82,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}一个被宏伟光环所围绕的世界\N{\fs13}a world encircled not only in majestic rings
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.86,0:00:32.36,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而且拥有数量众多的卫星\N{\fs13}but in an array of moons that have been likened
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.39,0:00:34.56,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}如同一个太阳系的缩影\N{\fs13}to a solar system in miniature.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.24,0:00:47.11,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}1997年，一项去往土星的国际任务拉开序幕\N{\fs13}In 1997, an international mission was launched to Saturn
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.14,0:00:49.71,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这将是首次\N{\fs13}that would, for the first time,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.74,0:00:53.58,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}试图把航天器送入土星轨道\N{\fs13}attempt to place an orbiting spacecraft around the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.62,0:00:57.92,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}还要将探测器降落外太阳系的卫星上\N{\fs13}and land a probe on a moon in the outer solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.99,0:01:02.16,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但这项任务\N{\fs13}But this was a mission that had to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.19,0:01:04.16,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}困难重重\N{\fs13}fight its way to the launch pad.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.66,0:01:06.89,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们的项目\N{\fs13}- [Lew] We're going to have to operate
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.93,0:01:08.56,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}面临非常严格的资金限制，\N{\fs13}under a very strict fund ceiling,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.60,0:01:11.27,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}此项法案会由国会强制实施\N{\fs13}one that is imposed by Congress.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.30,0:01:13.97,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因此需要一种与之前截然不同的方式\N{\fs13}- This will require doing business
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.00,0:01:17.51,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}来进行这项任务\N{\fs13}in a drastically different way than we've done before.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.54,0:01:21.38,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}[Bob]耗费大量时间，经过多轮谈判\N{\fs13}- [Bob] It took a lotta time, a lotta negotiating,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.41,0:01:24.28,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}做出很多妥协后才得以付诸实行\N{\fs13}a lot of compromises to make that work.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.31,0:01:27.18,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}第一次看到\N{\fs13}- [Julie] The first time I saw the spacecraft together
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.22,0:01:29.72,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}没有被遮布覆盖的飞船时，\N{\fs13}when we stacked without the blankets, we were just,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.75,0:01:32.35,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们都瞠目结舌\N{\fs13}we were without words standing out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.39,0:01:34.16,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}去土星的旅程\N{\fs13}- [Narrator] The journey to Saturn
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.19,0:01:36.52,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}需要七年之久，\N{\fs13}would take seven long years,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.56,0:01:41.06,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但决定它能否成功被土星捕获从而进入轨道的关键时间\N{\fs13}but the success, or failure, of being captured into orbit
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.10,0:01:45.83,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}只有短短的三个小时\N{\fs13}depended on what would happen during just three hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.13,0:01:49.07,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}[Charles]祈祷引擎最好能点火，\N{\fs13}- [Charles] The engine better fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.10,0:01:51.64,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}否则我们将以一次飞掠告终\N{\fs13}otherwise we'll end with a flyby.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.67,0:01:52.47,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}-收到\N{\fs13}- Copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.51,0:01:53.91,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}DCS故障保护\N{\fs13}DCS Fault Protection.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.94,0:01:55.98,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}[Linda]作为一名光环科学家，\N{\fs13}- [Linda] I think as a ring scientist,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.01,0:01:58.25,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我最担心的是\N{\fs13}my greatest concern was really crossing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.28,0:02:00.52,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}飞船通过F环和G环间隙的时刻\N{\fs13}through that gap in the F and G rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.55,0:02:04.35,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}只要一个弹珠大小的颗粒\N{\fs13}It would only have taken one marble sized particle
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.39,0:02:06.79,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}撞上飞船的关键位置\N{\fs13}in the wrong place in the spacecraft
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.82,0:02:09.32,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}大概任务就宣告结束了\N{\fs13}to perhaps have ended the mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.36,0:02:11.96,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以入夜时，我躺在床上想着：\N{\fs13}- [Man] So I would lie in bed at night and think about
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.99,0:02:14.16,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们还应该做哪些测试？\N{\fs13}what other tests should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.19,0:02:16.73,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我还应该问什么问题？\N{\fs13}What other question should I be asking?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.76,0:02:19.70,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}还需要查出哪些未完成的事项？\N{\fs13}What should we be poking out here that we haven't done yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.00,0:02:23.37,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}[Julie]我们追查一切可能出错的事情\N{\fs13}- [Julie] We chased everything that could go wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.40,0:02:24.67,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这非常困难\N{\fs13}down the rabbit hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.71,0:02:26.94,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们考虑每一种情况，如果这里出了问题，\N{\fs13}We went down every path of, if this goes wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.97,0:02:28.14,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们该怎么办？\N{\fs13}what do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.18,0:02:29.78,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}如果那里又出现问题，我们该怎么办？\N{\fs13}If that goes wrong, what do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.81,0:02:31.35,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}[Earl]这就是其中的一个关键时刻\N{\fs13}- [Earl] And this was one of those moments
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.38,0:02:33.38,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}要么成功进入轨道\N{\fs13}where you're either in orbit
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.41,0:02:35.48,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}要么数十亿美元打了水漂\N{\fs13}or you're a billion dollar flyby.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.52,0:02:37.59,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}[Todd]距抵达最接近点\N{\fs13}- [Todd] Closest approach is just a little over
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.62,0:02:39.02,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}还有两分钟出头\N{\fs13}two minutes away.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.05,0:02:42.66,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}预测今天的气温为-226华氏度，\N{\fs13}Predicted temps today, -226 degrees Fahrenheit,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.69,0:02:44.96,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}风速每小时1100英里\N{\fs13}winds of 1100 miles per hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.99,0:02:47.73,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那里的飓风和地球一样大\N{\fs13}Hurricanes the size of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.76,0:02:50.20,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}最好把卡西尼号的舱门关上\N{\fs13}Cassini would do well to batten down the hatches.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.38,0:02:57.42,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}土星上的胜利 第一部分：JPL 和太空时代
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.62,0:03:10.62,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}无奈之举*
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.62,0:03:16.66,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}土星曾经只是一个\N{\fs13}- [Narrator] Saturn was once but a single
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.69,0:03:19.13,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}夜空中的亮点，\N{\fs13}bright point of light in the night sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.66,0:03:24.17,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但在1610年，伽利略通过他的望远镜\N{\fs13}but in 1610 Galileo peered through his telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.20,0:03:26.10,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}看到了一些别的东西\N{\fs13}and saw something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.73,0:03:29.40,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}他认为在这个星球的两边，\N{\fs13}On either side of the planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.44,0:03:31.61,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}可能存在卫星\N{\fs13}he thought there might be moons.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.81,0:03:37.85,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}两年后，伽利略再次观测\N{\fs13}Two years later, Galileo looked again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.71,0:03:43.35,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}令他吃惊的是，这两个物体不见了\N{\fs13}To his astonishment, the two objects had disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.55,0:03:49.82,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}又过了两年，伽利略再次\N{\fs13}Another two years passed and Galileo again
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.86,0:03:51.89,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}将望远镜对准土星\N{\fs13}trained his telescope on Saturn.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.00,0:03:56.63,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}令人费解的凸出部分再次出现\N{\fs13}The puzzling bulges had returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.73,0:04:01.74,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这张图显示了伽利略\N{\fs13}This drawing shows how close Galileo came
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.77,0:04:02.94,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}距离谜题的答案有多近，\N{\fs13}to solving the riddle,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.54,0:04:08.58,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但他在不知道真相的情况下与世长辞\N{\fs13}but he went to his grave without ever knowing the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.68,0:04:13.78,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}半个世纪之后，荷兰科学家\N{\fs13}A half century would pass before the Dutch scientist
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.81,0:04:17.82,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}克里斯蒂安·惠更斯意识到这些凸起是圆环\N{\fs13}Christiaan Huygens realized the bulges were rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.69,0:04:23.16,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}至于它们时隐时现，\N{\fs13}As for their appearing and disappearing,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.19,0:04:26.59,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}惠更斯意识到这是由土星倾斜引起的\N{\fs13}Huygens realized that was caused by Saturn's tilting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.00,0:04:32.60,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}像地球一样，土星在其轴线上轻微地来回摆动\N{\fs13}Like Earth, Saturn gently rocks back and forth on its axis.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.90,0:04:38.84,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在黎明时分从地球上观测光环时，\N{\fs13}And when the rings are viewed from Earth at dawn,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.87,0:04:40.48,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它们几乎不可见\N{\fs13}they all but disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.98,0:04:47.15,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}随着时间的推移，土星逐渐进入我们的视野，\N{\fs13}As time passed, Saturn came into closer focus,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.42,0:04:53.22,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}1979年，NASA 的先驱者11号宇宙飞船\N{\fs13}and in 1979, NASA's Pioneer 11 spacecraft
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.25,0:04:55.92,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}为全世界带来了首次近距离的观测——\N{\fs13}gave the world the first closeup look
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.96,0:04:58.63,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}土星和它的光环\N{\fs13}at the planet and its rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.06,0:05:05.13,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}昨天下午我们收到了几张照片\N{\fs13}- We received several pictures yesterday afternoon
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.17,0:05:09.14,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}今晚，我们就快速浏览一遍\N{\fs13}and evening, and we'd like to run through some of those now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.17,0:05:11.54,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这就是那张\N{\fs13}This is the one that came in here
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.57,0:05:14.04,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}昨天下午三点左右传来的照片\N{\fs13}at about three o'clock yesterday afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.07,0:05:17.18,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这是我们目前拍到的\N{\fs13}This is by far the most spectacular picture
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.21,0:05:18.45,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}最壮观的一幅画面\N{\fs13}that we have so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.71,0:05:21.22,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这就是原始数据\N{\fs13}This is raw data.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.25,0:05:23.35,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}没有经过任何处理\N{\fs13}It has not been processed in any way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.75,0:05:28.09,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们可以看到这颗巨大的带环行星，当然，\N{\fs13}We can see the big banded planet and, of course,
