Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.04,0:27:27.17,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}联合测量木星的磁层，\N{\fs13}to jointly measure Jupiter's magnetosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.21,0:27:29.78,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}带电粒子的气泡被约束在\N{\fs13}a bubble of charged particles trapped*
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.81,0:27:32.51,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}行星的磁场中\N{\fs13}within the planet's magnetic field.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.65,0:27:37.68,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在最近的一次飞抵中，卡西尼号拍摄了这张照片\N{\fs13}At closest approach, Cassini took this image.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.72,0:27:42.26,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那时，我们看到了木星最详细的景象\N{\fs13}At that time, the most detailed view of Jupiter ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.03,0:27:58.04,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}和木星的相遇是一次全面的彩排\N{\fs13}The Jupiter encounter served as a full dress rehearsal
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.07,0:27:59.71,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}一切都为土星准备\N{\fs13}for what awaited at Saturn.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.94,0:28:02.51,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这暴露了不足之处：\N{\fs13}It revealed there was work to be done
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.54,0:28:05.71,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}卡西尼号在设计上有妥协\N{\fs13}in addressing Cassini's design compromise.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.75,0:28:08.61,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}缺少了扫描平台\N{\fs13}The lack of the scan platform that would have allowed
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.65,0:28:11.22,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}就不能同时使用\N{\fs13}simultaneous use of science instruments,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.25,0:28:14.82,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}需要移动和需要静止的科学仪器\N{\fs13}needing either to move or to be rock steady.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.96,0:28:18.83,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这意味着每次想把仪器对准某处\N{\fs13}- It meant you had to turn the spacecraft
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.86,0:28:21.76,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}都必须旋转整个飞船 \N{\fs13}every time you wanted to point an instrument someplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.79,0:28:24.56,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们有12种仪器，\N{\fs13}And we had 12 instruments,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.60,0:28:27.20,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而且每种仪器一般都有需求\N{\fs13}and each instrument generally had
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.23,0:28:30.24,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}就算不是严格的快速指向要求\N{\fs13}different pointing druthers, if not in fact,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.27,0:28:32.64,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}也需要不同的指向选择\N{\fs13}hard and fast pointing requirements.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.67,0:28:35.34,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}于是在不同的科学团队之间\N{\fs13}And so there was an awful lot of negotiation
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.37,0:28:38.28,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}进行了大量的交涉\N{\fs13}that went on between the different science teams,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.31,0:28:41.28,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}仪器负责人们相互谈判，\N{\fs13}the different instrument representatives,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.31,0:28:43.45,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}决定出谁有权控制\N{\fs13}in deciding who was gonna get to control
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.48,0:28:45.89,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}飞船的指向\N{\fs13}the pointing of the spacecraft when.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.92,0:28:49.32,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}经过很长时间，多次谈判，\N{\fs13}It took a lot of time, a lot of negotiating,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.36,0:28:52.13,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}为了让项目运转，我们做出了很多妥协\N{\fs13}a lot of compromises to make that work.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.73,0:28:57.36,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}尽管有着如此限制，\N{\fs13}- [Narrator] Despite this restraint,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.40,0:29:00.23,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}卡西尼号现在可以自豪地说\N{\fs13}Cassini could now boast of being the most capable
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.27,0:29:03.24,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}自己是人类向太阳系发射的\N{\fs13}interplanetary spacecraft ever sent out
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.27,0:29:04.70,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}功能最强大的飞船\N{\fs13}into the solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.70,0:29:19.70,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}土星轨道插入
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.42,0:29:27.36,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}经过近七年的旅程，\N{\fs13}After a journey of nearly seven years,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.39,0:29:31.83,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}卡西尼-惠更斯号探测器和土星已经近在咫尺\N{\fs13}Cassini and the Huygens probe are nearing Saturn's doorstep.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.86,0:29:34.80,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}二十年的梦想，规划，\N{\fs13}Whether two decades of dreaming, planning,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.83,0:29:38.17,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}建设和承担这一艰巨的旅行的工作\N{\fs13}building, and undertaking this arduous journey
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.20,0:29:41.67,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}是否能得到回报，即将见分晓\N{\fs13}will be rewarded, will soon be known.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.71,0:29:44.84,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为卡西尼号\N{\fs13}For just ahead is the most dangerous moment
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.88,0:29:47.01,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}即将面临最危险的时刻\N{\fs13}that Cassini will face.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.05,0:29:48.85,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}SOI \N{\fs13}SOI.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.88,0:29:50.88,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}土星轨道插入\N{\fs13}Saturn Orbit Insertion.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.82,0:29:57.79,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这一刻，没有人比查尔斯·埃拉奇\N{\fs13}No one is more excited, or anxious, about this moment
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.82,0:29:59.96,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}更加激动和焦虑\N{\fs13}than Charles Elachi.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.99,0:30:02.66,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}除了担任卡西尼号的\N{\fs13}In addition to still being the team lead
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.70,0:30:04.86,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}的雷达实验团队的领导外，\N{\fs13}for Cassini's radar experiment,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.90,0:30:06.57,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}现在他还主管 JPL\N{\fs13}he now heads JPL.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.60,0:30:10.50,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}卡西尼号可能是美国承办的\N{\fs13}- Cassini is probably one of the most exciting missions
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.54,0:30:15.54,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}最令人兴奋的任务之一，它值得更多的赞扬\N{\fs13}ever undertaken by the US and it deserves more credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.74,0:30:19.14,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以当我们进入轨道插入阶段，\N{\fs13}So when we come to the orbit insertion,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.18,0:30:21.65,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}经过之前的提议，游说，\N{\fs13}after advocating for it, selling it,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.68,0:30:24.68,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}建造，飞行阶段\N{\fs13}building it and flying it,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.72,0:30:27.62,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}现在该打起精神了\N{\fs13}it was a really very sobering moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.22,0:30:33.83,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}引擎最好能点火，否则我们会以飞掠告终\N{\fs13}The engine better fire, otherwise we'll end with a fly by.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.29,0:30:38.30,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}必须记住火星观察者号的前车之鉴，\N{\fs13}You have to remember that we had the Mars Observer,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.33,0:30:41.43,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当我们打开引擎时，飞船就不见了\N{\fs13}where when we turned on the engine, the thing disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.10,0:30:45.97,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}11年前，\N{\fs13}- [Narrator] 11 years before,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.01,0:30:48.64,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当火星观察者号接近火星时，\N{\fs13}as Mars Observer was approaching Mars,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.67,0:30:51.31,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}飞船被命令\N{\fs13}the spacecraft was commanded to pressurize
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.34,0:30:52.85,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}给推进系统加压\N{\fs13}its propulsion system.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.28,0:30:57.42,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那艘宇宙飞船再也没有音讯了\N{\fs13}The spacecraft was never heard from again.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.22,0:31:03.52,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}据说是燃料管发生了严重断裂，\N{\fs13}It's believed a massive rupture in the fuel lines occurred,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.56,0:31:07.46,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}使宇宙飞船处于无法恢复的旋转状态\N{\fs13}putting the spacecraft into an unrecoverable spin.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.60,0:31:14.50,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们大约有15到20分钟的时间\N{\fs13}We have about 15, 20 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.53,0:31:17.17,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这是鲍勃·米切尔，他是项目经理\N{\fs13}This is Bob Mitchell, who is the project manager.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.60,0:31:20.91,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}好吧，好吧，我想我们已经知道了\N{\fs13}- Okay, well, I think we've got what'll be
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.94,0:31:23.44,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}今晚这里会有一个\N{\fs13}a rather interesting program laid out here
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.48,0:31:24.71,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}相当有趣的节目\N{\fs13}for you this evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.74,0:31:27.38,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}当然会包含一点戏剧性\N{\fs13}Certainly gonna have a little drama to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.41,0:31:32.25,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我对此相当自信，但还是有些担心\N{\fs13}I was kinda confident, but I was worried, concerned.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.69,0:31:36.26,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}“紧张”可能是最好的形容\N{\fs13}Nervous might be the best word as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.03,0:31:43.50,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}需要降低速度\N{\fs13}- [Narrator] To slow down enough to be captured
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.53,0:31:45.10,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}才能被土星的引力捕获，\N{\fs13}by Saturn's gravity,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.13,0:31:48.64,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}卡西尼号必须要启动不常用的引擎\N{\fs13}Cassini will have to turn on its seldom used engine
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.67,0:31:50.90,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}共计96分钟\N{\fs13}for 96 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.94,0:31:54.14,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}低于这个时间就会飞过这个星球，\N{\fs13}Anything less could result in flying past the planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.11,0:31:56.51,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}一去不返\N{\fs13}never to return.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.38,0:32:03.85,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}飞行路线将引导卡西尼号和探测器\N{\fs13}The flight path will take Cassini and the probe
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.88,0:32:08.22,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在土星光环的缝隙中上下穿梭\N{\fs13}up through and back down a gap in Saturn's rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.25,0:32:10.06,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}人们担心在这些区域\N{\fs13}There's worry that there could be particles
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.09,0:32:12.39,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}可能会有粒子造成破坏\N{\fs13}in these regions large enough to damage,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.43,0:32:16.23,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}甚至摧毁飞船\N{\fs13}or even destroy, the spacecraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.26,0:32:18.00,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}作为一名光环科学家，\N{\fs13}- I think as a ring scientist,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.03,0:32:21.07,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我最关心的是如何穿越这个\N{\fs13}my greatest concern was really crossing through that gap
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.10,0:32:23.07,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}F环和G环之间的缝隙\N{\fs13}in the F and G rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.10,0:32:26.91,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}只要一个弹珠大小的颗粒\N{\fs13}It would only have taken one marble sized particle
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.94,0:32:28.87,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}撞上飞船的关键位置\N{\fs13}in the wrong place in the spacecraft
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.91,0:32:30.68,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}大概任务就可以宣告结束了\N{\fs13}to perhaps have ended the mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.71,0:32:33.65,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以对我来说，最惊险的\N{\fs13}So for me, the most, you know, breathtaking,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.68,0:32:35.51,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}心跳停止的时刻\N{\fs13}the heart stopping time, was really
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.55,0:32:37.25,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}就是穿过土星环平面的时候\N{\fs13}crossing through the ring plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.08,0:32:40.85,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}为了降低风险，\N{\fs13}- [Narrator] To reduce the risk,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.89,0:32:44.16,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}卡西尼号将用它的高增益天线指向前方\N{\fs13}Cassini will fly through the gaps with its high gain antenna
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.19,0:32:47.49,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}充当穿越缝隙时的盾牌 \N{\fs13}facing forward to act as a shield.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.53,0:32:50.30,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在这些时间里，唯一能返回地球的\N{\fs13}During these times, the only signal coming back to Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.33,0:32:55.00,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}将是从较小的天线发射出的单一频率信号\N{\fs13}will be from a smaller antenna transmitting a single tone.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.03,0:32:58.24,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}信号的波长或频率\N{\fs13}The pitch, or frequency, of the tone will vary
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.27,0:33:01.14,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}随着飞船速度的变化会有所不同\N{\fs13}with changes to the spacecraft's speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.17,0:33:03.38,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这就是多普勒效应\N{\fs13}What's known as the Doppler effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.78,0:33:07.85,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这将告诉工程师飞船运行正常\N{\fs13}This will tell engineers how the spacecraft is performing...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.85,0:33:10.35,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}还是失控\N{\fs13}or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.38,0:33:12.79,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}-零是参考频率，\N{\fs13}- Zero is the reference frequency,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.82,0:33:14.95,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}如果引擎点火失败，\N{\fs13}the nominal frequency that we would see
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.99,0:33:16.59,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们将看到这个标准频率\N{\fs13}if there were no burn.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.62,0:33:18.22,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以如果发动机没有点火，\N{\fs13}So if the motor never ignited,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.26,0:33:20.43,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这张图上将会显示\N{\fs13}what would happen is this line up here
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.46,0:33:22.96,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}一条横向的直线\N{\fs13}would just go right straight across.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.00,0:33:24.73,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以入夜时，我躺在床上想着：\N{\fs13}I would lie in bed at night and think about
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.76,0:33:27.30,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们还应该做哪些测试？\N{\fs13}what other tests should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.33,0:33:29.84,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我还应该问什么问题？\N{\fs13}What other question should I be asking?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.87,0:33:32.74,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}还需要查出哪些未完成的事项？\N{\fs13}What should we be poking at here that we haven't done yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.77,0:33:35.58,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这里的这个尖角对应于\N{\fs13}And this corner right here corresponds to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.61,0:33:37.44,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}点火结束的时刻\N{\fs13}where the burn should end.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.48,0:33:40.68,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我不可能知晓\N{\fs13}There wasn't any single thing that I could point to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.71,0:33:42.65,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}哪些特定的事情\N{\fs13}and say that thing right there
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.68,0:33:44.88,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}将要出差错\N{\fs13}has a fair chance of biting us.*
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.92,0:33:46.69,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这根本就不可能做到\N{\fs13}There just wasn't anything like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.72,0:33:51.12,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但是你必须考虑所有预期的情况…\N{\fs13}But when you consider all the things that had to happen...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.16,0:33:53.33,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}以及非预期的情况，\N{\fs13}or not happen,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.36,0:33:56.63,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}需要考量的条件太多\N{\fs13}there were enough of them that the aggregate of them
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.66,0:33:58.56,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}足以让人焦虑\N{\fs13}was cause for being nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.60,0:33:59.80,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我正是如此\N{\fs13}And I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.83,0:34:03.14,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这时就要引起关注了\N{\fs13}That would be cause for some level of concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.61,0:34:13.78,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}SOI是一项团队工作\N{\fs13}- [Julie] SOI was such a, just such a team effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.98,0:34:16.75,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们追查一切可能出错的事情\N{\fs13}We chased everything that could go wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.78,0:34:18.02,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这非常困难\N{\fs13}down the rabbit hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.05,0:34:20.29,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们考虑每一种情况，如果这里出了问题，\N{\fs13}We went down every path of, if this goes wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.32,0:34:21.45,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们该怎么办？\N{\fs13}what do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.49,0:34:23.29,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}如果那里又出现问题，我们该怎么办？\N{\fs13}If that goes wrong, what do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.32,0:34:28.33,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}共运行了10000个用例来测试轨道插入\N{\fs13}There were 10,000 tests run to put together that insertion.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.83,0:34:35.00,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这是我们一直在准备的东西\N{\fs13}- Something we've been preparing for
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.03,0:34:38.54,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}经过了四五年的不断测试，\N{\fs13}for four or five years, testing and testing,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.57,0:34:41.94,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}包括各种可能的极端情况\N{\fs13}awfulizing all of the possible things that could go wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.97,0:34:45.58,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这是就是关键时刻之一\N{\fs13}And this was one of those moments where you're either
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.61,0:34:48.31,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}要么进入轨道，要么数十亿美元打水漂\N{\fs13}in orbit or you're a billion dollar fly by.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.79,0:34:59.36,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}卡西尼号任务控制中心状况良好\N{\fs13}- Things continue to go well in Cassini mission control.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.39,0:35:02.93,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}离点火开始还有约33分钟\N{\fs13}We're approximately 33 minutes from burn start.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.96,0:35:05.13,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这是我们的飞行总监朱莉·韦伯斯特\N{\fs13}There's our flight director, Julie Webster.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.60,0:35:09.57,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这位是我们今晚不希望听到发言的人：\N{\fs13}This is one person we hope to not hear from tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.60,0:35:13.37,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}系统故障保护工程师Paula Morgan\N{\fs13}This is system fault protection engineer, Paula Morgan.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.41,0:35:15.34,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}如果我们收到故障保护信息，\N{\fs13}And if we hear from fault protection,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.37,0:35:18.04,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这意味着我们在飞船上发现了某种异常情况\N{\fs13}that means we've had some sort of anomaly on the spacecraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.08,0:35:21.18,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}道格·约翰逊，我们的无线电科学和SOI通讯员\N{\fs13}Doug Johnson, our radio science and SOI communicator.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.21,0:35:23.82,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}今晚我们将从他那里通过多普勒信号\N{\fs13}He's the one reporting most of the events we'll see tonight
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.85,0:35:25.25,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}收到大部分事件的播报\N{\fs13}through that Doppler signal.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.39,0:35:29.42,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}控制台上的简·伯克利\N{\fs13}- [Narrator] Also on console is Jan Berkeley.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.45,0:35:32.72,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}最初在JPL工作时是一名大学实习生\N{\fs13}She first worked at JPL as a college intern.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.76,0:35:36.13,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}现在她是卡西尼小组的关键成员\N{\fs13}Now she's a key member of the Cassini team
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.16,0:35:38.50,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}负责创建计算机指令序列\N{\fs13}that creates the computer sequence commands
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.53,0:35:40.93,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}来操纵飞船\N{\fs13}that operate the spacecraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.97,0:35:42.70,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们会运行指令，\N{\fs13}- We would run them, make sure that there were
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.73,0:35:44.20,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}确保程序没有问题\N{\fs13}no problems with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.24,0:35:46.64,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}如果需要做测试，我们会安排\N{\fs13}If we needed to do testing, we would schedule testing.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.67,0:35:49.21,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们才是真正把命令送到宇宙飞船的人\N{\fs13}We were the ones that actually sent them to the spacecraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.24,0:35:51.04,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}然后等待指令生效\N{\fs13}And then we watched them clock out.*
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.08,0:35:53.38,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}最紧张的时刻不是按下发送按钮，\N{\fs13}That was the tense moment, was not pushing the button,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.41,0:35:55.98,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而是等待它传回生效的信息\N{\fs13}it was waiting for it to come back, that it worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.38,0:36:00.69,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而土星离我们太远了，光是信号的往返时间\N{\fs13}And Saturn was so far away that it would take three hours
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.72,0:36:02.49,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}就需要三个小时\N{\fs13}just to get there and come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.66,0:36:05.72,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}卡西尼号航天器的当前速度：\N{\fs13}- Current speed of the Cassini spacecraft:
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.76,0:36:08.16,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}每秒22.2公里，\N{\fs13}22.2 kilometers per second,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.19,0:36:10.70,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}每小时不到50000英里\N{\fs13}which is just under 50,000 miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.73,0:36:14.10,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}随着土星的引力增长，速度还在增加\N{\fs13}And increasing as Saturn's gravity draws us in.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.13,0:36:17.90,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那是Shin Huh，我们的SOI系统工程师\N{\fs13}That's Shin Huh, our SOI systems engineer.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.94,0:36:21.51,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}他日日夜夜研究 SOI\N{\fs13}Shin has eaten, breathed, slept, and lived SOI
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.54,0:36:23.08,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}已有多年\N{\fs13}for many years.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.11,0:36:25.54,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}今晚是他的关键时刻\N{\fs13}Tonight is his big night.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.58,0:36:28.01,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}SOI系统上的所有岗位\N{\fs13}- All stations on that SOI systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.05,0:36:29.82,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}只是提醒一下，我们即将准时到达\N{\fs13}Just an advisory, we're coming up on the time
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.85,0:36:32.08,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为关键的\N{\fs13}for the critical sequence will initiate the turn
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.12,0:36:33.62,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}SOI 点火姿态序列将要启动\N{\fs13}to the SOI burn attitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.65,0:36:38.39,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}点火命令将在当地时间下午7:35:35发送\N{\fs13}The burn command will be sent at 7:35:35 PM local time.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.36,0:36:41.86,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}SOI系统飞行总监，\N{\fs13}Flight director, SOI systems,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.89,0:36:44.66,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所有子系统报告航天器参数达标\N{\fs13}all subsystems report the spacecraft data is nominal
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.70,0:36:46.63,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}并准备支持进行SOI\N{\fs13}and ready to support SOI.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.67,0:36:47.90,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}好的，我知道了\N{\fs13}- [Man] Okay, I copy that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.18,0:37:00.85,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}SOI，飞行通信总监\N{\fs13}SOI, comms flight director...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.18,0:37:03.18,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们待命中\N{\fs13}- [Todd] We're waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.22,0:37:04.05,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}复制通信\N{\fs13}- Copy telecomm*
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.86,0:37:20.57,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}JPL的传统活动\N{\fs13}A JPL tradition has begun,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.60,0:37:22.74,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}从任务支援区后方开始\N{\fs13}starting in the back of the Mission Support Area.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.77,0:37:26.44,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这是JPL的幸运花生时间\N{\fs13}This is the consuming of the lucky JPL peanuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.61,0:37:36.75,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}道格·约翰逊刚刚报告了一个信号，\N{\fs13}Doug Johnson just reported a signal,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.78,0:37:38.42,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们在穿越土星环时幸存了下来\N{\fs13}we've survived the ring plane crossing
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.45,0:37:40.12,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}已经通过F环和G环\N{\fs13}through the F and G rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.83,0:37:49.13,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}一波未平一波又起，\N{\fs13}One hurdle down, one to go, with the start of the burn*
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.16,0:37:51.33,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}引擎将在9分钟后点火\N{\fs13}a meer nine minutes away.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.36,0:37:54.17,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}FSL 的飞行总监\N{\fs13}- [Julie] ACE flight director on FSL court.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.20,0:37:57.34,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你还在B2频道追踪堪培拉(CDSCC)吗？\N{\fs13}Are you still tracking Canberra on B2?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.07,0:38:01.31,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}是的\N{\fs13}- [Man] That's affirmative.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.34,0:38:03.74,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}继续，把堪培拉切换到B-Zero\N{\fs13}- Let's go ahead and switch Canberra over to B-Zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.02,0:38:11.48,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}继续，导航一号\N{\fs13}Go ahead, NAV-1.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.52,0:38:13.52,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们可以确认收到了\N{\fs13}- [Man] We can confirm that we are receiving
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.55,0:38:14.89,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}来自DSN的单向数据\N{\fs13}one way data from the DSN.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.06,0:38:18.96,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}DSS14的单向多普勒？\N{\fs13}- [Julie] One way Doppler from DSS14?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.99,0:38:20.86,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}是的\N{\fs13}- [Man] Yes, that's affirmative.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.20,0:38:25.70,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}导航也可以确认收到了\N{\fs13}- Navigation can also confirm we're receiving
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.73,0:38:27.20,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}多普勒数据\N{\fs13}the Doppler data.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.23,0:38:29.20,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们已经证实了这个\N{\fs13}We've been able to verify that the turn
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.24,0:38:31.44,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}转向 SY-burn 的姿态已经完成 \N{\fs13}to the SY burn attitude is complete.*
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.47,0:38:35.61,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}离SOI点火还有两分钟\N{\fs13}We're approaching two minutes before the SOI burn.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.64,0:38:38.34,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}成千上万科学家和工程师们的希望和梦想\N{\fs13}Hopes and dreams of thousands of scientists
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.38,0:38:41.65,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}将静待接下来的几分钟的结局\N{\fs13}and engineers are resting on the next few moments.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.68,0:38:43.88,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}祝你好运，卡西尼惠更斯号\N{\fs13}So Godspeed, Cassini Huygens.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.92,0:38:45.12,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}期望能在轨道上看到你\N{\fs13}May we see you in orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.45,0:38:47.55,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们要去看看\N{\fs13}- We're gonna drop in.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.26,0:38:51.29,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在多普勒显示上，我们预期的是\N{\fs13}- On the Doppler display, what we're looking for
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.32,0:38:54.29,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}沿着那条线\N{\fs13}is a turning of the corner to start to follow that line
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.33,0:38:56.19,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}折向右下角\N{\fs13}down to the lower right.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.23,0:38:58.46,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这就是点火开始的迹象\N{\fs13}And that's our indication the burn has begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.77,0:39:03.97,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}飞行控制，这里是SOI通信..\N{\fs13}Flight, SOI comms..
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.00,0:39:05.44,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}说吧\N{\fs13}- [Julie] Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.47,0:39:07.77,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们收到了\N{\fs13}- [Man] We have a Doppler signature consistent
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.81,0:39:09.71,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}引擎点火的多普勒信号\N{\fs13}with engine turn on.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.15,0:39:22.82,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}任务控制中心\N{\fs13}- [Todd] Lots of high fives and celebrations
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.86,0:39:23.82,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}都在击掌和庆祝\N{\fs13}in mission control.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.33,0:39:31.60,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}祝贺为了此刻\N{\fs13}Congratulations all of you that have worked so hard
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.63,0:39:32.47,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所有辛勤工作的人\N{\fs13}for this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.44,0:39:40.64,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}已经过了一分钟，总计需要96分钟\N{\fs13}One minute down, about 96 minutes to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.48,0:39:47.81,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们将继续沿着预期曲线\N{\fs13}We're continuing to follow the nominal predicted curve
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.85,0:39:48.78,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在多普勒图上行进\N{\fs13}on the Doppler.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.81,0:39:49.95,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以事实上我们已经经过拐角\N{\fs13}So the fact we turned the corner
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.98,0:39:51.18,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}表示引擎已启动\N{\fs13}means the engine has started.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.22,0:39:52.65,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}事实上，我们正在遵循这条路线\N{\fs13}The fact that we're following the line
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.68,0:39:54.29,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}意味着我们从引擎中获得了正确的推力\N{\fs13}means we're getting the right thrust out of the engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.32,0:39:57.32,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}卡西尼-惠更斯号飞船还将传来更多的好消息\N{\fs13}So more good news for the Cassini Huygens spacecraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.90,0:40:07.83,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}-干得好\N{\fs13}- Way to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.87,0:40:09.30,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}干得好\N{\fs13}Way to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.34,0:40:11.97,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}-现在需要经过90分钟的等待\N{\fs13}- [Narrator] There's now 90 minutes of waiting
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.00,0:40:14.91,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}直到卡西尼号的引擎停止工作\N{\fs13}until Cassini's engine is to stop firing.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.94,0:40:18.31,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}行动的空当提供了一个难得的机会\N{\fs13}The lull in the action affords a rare opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.34,0:40:20.81,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}给在场的国会议员\N{\fs13}to give members of Congress who are on hand
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.85,0:40:23.72,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}提供一次非常近距离的私人参观机会\N{\fs13}a very up close and personal tour.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.93,0:40:39.86,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这是见证历史的时刻，\N{\fs13}It's a moment to witness history in the making,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.90,0:40:42.17,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}正如政治家们深知的，\N{\fs13}and, as politicians well-know,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.20,0:40:45.24,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}需要利用优秀的摄影作品来记录\N{\fs13}to take advantage of an excellent photo op.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.51,0:40:54.51,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}NASA 卡西尼号任务控制中心，现在是晚上7点42分\N{\fs13}- It's 7:42 PM in NASA's Cassini mission control.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.92,0:40:59.52,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}接下来我们预期在 A 环发生“掩星”现象\N{\fs13}The next thing we'll look for is an occultation
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.55,0:41:03.56,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}太平洋时间当地时间晚上8点05分左右\N{\fs13}by the A ring around 8:05 PM Pacific time local.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.59,0:41:06.16,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那时，在多普勒信号中\N{\fs13}At that time, we'll see an increased noise
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.19,0:41:07.69,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们会看到噪音增加，\N{\fs13}in the Doppler signal,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.73,0:41:11.03,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}与多普勒图最左边部分\N{\fs13}similar to the increased noise there at the far left
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.06,0:41:12.40,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}增加的噪音类似\N{\fs13}of the Doppler plot.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.43,0:41:15.27,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}还有今晚最后的惊悚时刻：\N{\fs13}And our final scary moment of the evening
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.30,0:41:17.84,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}需要确保引擎停止燃烧\N{\fs13}will be to make sure to get the burn shut down.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.30,0:41:22.48,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这将是为JPL、NASA和全世界创造历史的一天\N{\fs13}The history making day for JPL, NASA, and the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.81,0:41:27.11,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}飞行控制，SOI通信\N{\fs13}- [Man] Flight, SOI comm.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.15,0:41:28.68,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}-继续，SOI通信\N{\fs13}- Go ahead, SOI comm.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.71,0:41:31.85,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们正好通过了A环\N{\fs13}- [Man] We have hit the A ring pretty hard.*
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.88,0:41:33.62,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}-好的\N{\fs13}- All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.65,0:41:36.05,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}SOI 通信那边有更多好消息，\N{\fs13}- [Todd] More good news from SOI Comm there,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.09,0:41:39.06,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们的多普勒数据图上发生了可怕的变化\N{\fs13}the frightening looking change to our Doppler data
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.09,0:41:40.76,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但这完全是意料之中的事\N{\fs13}is totally anticipated.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.79,0:41:42.96,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这证明了土星的A环与预期一致\N{\fs13}This proves that Saturn's A ring is where we think it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.99,0:41:46.97,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}卡西尼号飞船也同样尽在掌握\N{\fs13}And the Cassini spacecraft is where we think it is as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.70,0:41:52.27,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们继续跟踪2到3分贝的信号\N{\fs13}- [Man] We're continuing to track a two to three DB signal
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.30,0:41:55.21,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}通过A环时偶尔会中断\N{\fs13}with occasional outages through the A ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.24,0:41:56.41,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们希望看到一个很清晰的强烈信号，\N{\fs13}And we expect to see a nice strong signal,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.44,0:41:58.74,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们马上就要到关键部分了\N{\fs13}we have the main division coming up.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.78,0:42:00.25,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}收到，听起来不错\N{\fs13}- [Julie] Copy that, sounds good.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.78,0:42:08.42,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们看到，飞船正在接近B环，\N{\fs13}- [Todd] As we see, we're approaching the B ring,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.89,0:42:12.19,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}必须记住今晚我们看见的这一切\N{\fs13}and we must remember tonight, everything happening at Saturn
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.22,0:42:14.29,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}都发生在一小时24分钟之前\N{\fs13}occurred an hour and 24 minutes earlier
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.33,0:42:17.86,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}都怪那讨厌的每秒186000英里的光速，\N{\fs13}due to that pesky speed of light, 186,000 miles per second,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.90,0:42:20.40,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}限制了我们的星际通信速度\N{\fs13}our interplanetary speed limit, if you will.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.43,0:42:22.07,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}SOI通信，继续\N{\fs13}- [Julie] Go ahead SOI Comm.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.10,0:42:24.24,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在达到11分贝的短暂峰值后，\N{\fs13}- [Man] After a brief peak up to 11DB,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.27,0:42:27.47,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们现在已离开该部分\N{\fs13}we have now exited the division.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.51,0:42:28.47,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}-收到\N{\fs13}- Copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.51,0:42:30.84,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}刚才发生了什么事？\N{\fs13}- [Man] What just happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.88,0:42:33.78,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}他们刚刚宣布我们现在\N{\fs13}- They just announced that we are now
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.81,0:42:35.98,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}已经被土星捕获\N{\fs13}a captured object around Saturn.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.01,0:42:38.25,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们现在是一个轨道...轨道飞行器\N{\fs13}We are now an orbit... an orbiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.52,0:42:42.22,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}历史上第一个土星轨道飞行器\N{\fs13}- First in history around Saturn.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.25,0:42:43.36,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}如你所见\N{\fs13}- There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.39,0:42:45.22,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}第一个环绕土星的人造轨道飞行器\N{\fs13}First man-made orbiter around Saturn.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.42,0:42:48.43,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}旅行者号，羡慕吧\N{\fs13}Voyager, eat your heart out.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.33,0:42:52.36,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}SOI系统，这是意外事件\N{\fs13}- [Man] SOI systems, this is contingency.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.00,0:42:56.90,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}还有两分钟多一点就要到达最接近点\N{\fs13}- Closest approach is just a little over two minutes away.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.94,0:42:59.67,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}考虑到这一点，可能是时候开始\N{\fs13}And given that, it's probably about time
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.71,0:43:02.41,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们的土星天气预报\N{\fs13}for our Saturnian weather forecast.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.44,0:43:06.28,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}预测今天的气温为-226华氏度\N{\fs13}Predicted temps today, -226 degrees Fahrenheit
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.31,0:43:09.18,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}或-143摄氏度\N{\fs13}or -143 degrees Celsius.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.21,0:43:12.55,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}风速每小时1100英里左右\N{\fs13}Winds of 1100 miles per hour or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.58,0:43:16.96,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}内部出现氦雨的可能性为100%\N{\fs13}Chance of helium rain inside the interior, 100%.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.99,0:43:19.49,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}还会有地球大小的飓风\N{\fs13}Hurricanes the size of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.52,0:43:22.16,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}卡西尼号最好把舱门关上\N{\fs13}Cassini would do well to batten down the hatches.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.16,0:43:27.27,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}正以极快的速度进行最近的一次抵近\N{\fs13}Closest approach is upon us with a speed
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.30,0:43:29.70,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}速度几乎达到每小时69000英里\N{\fs13}of almost 69,000 miles per hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.73,0:43:32.20,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而且已经开始减速\N{\fs13}And the speed HAS started slowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.63,0:44:03.87,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}飞行控制，这里是SOI通讯\N{\fs13}- [Man] Flight, SOI Comm.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.90,0:44:05.14,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}请说，SOI通讯\N{\fs13}- [Julie] Go ahead, SOI Comm.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.17,0:44:08.27,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}多普勒图已经变平了\N{\fs13}- [Man] The Doppler has flattened out.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.35,0:44:21.85,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}好的，用于SOI的引擎\N{\fs13}- [Todd] Okay, we have burn complete here,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.89,0:44:23.52,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}已经停止燃烧了\N{\fs13}for the SOI orbit insertion burn.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.26,0:44:31.20,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}任务控制中心都在祝贺\N{\fs13}Congratulations continue in mission control.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.23,0:44:33.06,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}击掌声从后面的\N{\fs13}The high-fives begin in the back
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.10,0:44:34.50,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}任务支援区传来\N{\fs13}of our mission support area.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.11,0:44:46.08,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我刚从无线电里听到消息...\N{\fs13}I'm just hearing a report from radio...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.01,0:44:50.15,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}-你做得很好\N{\fs13}- You did great.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.18,0:44:51.42,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你做得很好非常感谢\N{\fs13}You did great. - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.45,0:44:52.68,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}-不客气\N{\fs13}- My pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.72,0:44:55.92,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}为我们幸运的推进工程师们干杯\N{\fs13}Here's to our lucky propulsion engineers.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.82,0:44:57.99,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}今晚的工作非常出色\N{\fs13}Did a wonderful job tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.02,0:45:00.22,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}-知道它幸存了下来\N{\fs13}- Knowing that it survived and was there
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.26,0:45:01.79,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们已经准备好了\N{\fs13}and we were ready to, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.83,0:45:04.83,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}开始进入科学部分，获取伟大的图像\N{\fs13}get to the meat of the science and get these great images.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.86,0:45:05.90,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那是一个美妙的时刻\N{\fs13}It was a wonderful moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.93,0:45:07.23,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}旅程开始了\N{\fs13}The voyage begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.27,0:45:08.77,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们成功了，我们做到了\N{\fs13}We made it, like, we did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.91,0:45:14.54,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}-干得好\N{\fs13}- Fantastic job.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.57,0:45:16.58,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}现在我们要把你的ECAP纳入考核\N{\fs13}- Now we're gonna put your ECAP in.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.38,0:45:22.81,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我的领导刚刚通知我，\N{\fs13}- [Todd] I was just informed by my management,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.85,0:45:25.28,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}她会把我的绩效评估纳入考核\N{\fs13}she'll put my performance evaluation in.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.32,0:45:27.62,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我很高兴她等到今晚成功后才这么做\N{\fs13}I'm glad she waited until our success tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.69,0:45:30.56,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它活下来了\N{\fs13}It's alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.59,0:45:31.72,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它活下来了\N{\fs13}- It's alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.72,0:45:51.72,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}土星环
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.41,0:45:54.61,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}先是一场狂欢\N{\fs13}- So there's this amazing elation
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.65,0:45:57.65,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}紧接着就沉寂下来，\N{\fs13}and then almost immediately a crash,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.68,0:46:00.89,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为我们都精疲力竭\N{\fs13}just because we're exhausted and tired,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.92,0:46:02.42,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但是我睡不着\N{\fs13}but I couldn't sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.45,0:46:04.62,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以我留在了MSA，\N{\fs13}And so I stayed in the MSA,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.66,0:46:09.49,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}光环的图像在回放，\N{\fs13}and the images of the rings were playing back,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.53,0:46:14.03,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}慢慢地，人们开始聚集在这些图像周围，\N{\fs13}and slowly people started to gather around these images,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.07,0:46:16.70,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这些在飞过光环的顶端时拍摄的特写镜头\N{\fs13}which no one had seen close up images
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.73,0:46:18.74,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}之前从未有人见过\N{\fs13}flying right over the tops of the rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.37,0:46:24.28,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我只觉得心潮起伏\N{\fs13}And there were just goosebumps.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.31,0:46:26.18,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那是我永远难忘的记忆\N{\fs13}That's a memory I will never forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.28,0:46:32.02,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这是更多的小环，小片\N{\fs13}- This is way more ringlets, little pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.05,0:46:34.05,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}到目前为止，任务主要是\N{\fs13}- [Narrator] Until now, the mission has been
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.09,0:46:36.39,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}工程师的领域\N{\fs13}mostly the province of engineers.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.42,0:46:40.13,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}从这些土星光环的第一张特写照片开始，\N{\fs13}With these first ever closeup images of Saturn's rings,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.16,0:46:43.39,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}项目郑重地转向科学领域\N{\fs13}the shift to science begins in earnest,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.43,0:46:46.96,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}从已知情况来看，\N{\fs13}and there are hints of major discoveries ahead
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.00,0:46:48.73,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}未来还有重大发现的迹象\N{\fs13}from what already can be seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.90,0:46:52.67,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我认为即使不是一个光环科学家\N{\fs13}- I don't think you have to be a ring scientist
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.70,0:46:55.24,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}也能理解昨晚对我们来说意味着什么\N{\fs13}to imagine what last night was for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.27,0:46:57.98,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}真是无以言表\N{\fs13}It was beyond description really.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.01,0:46:59.54,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}真是震撼心灵\N{\fs13}It was mind blowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.58,0:47:02.11,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这是你能想到的所有形容词\N{\fs13}It was every adjective you could think of.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.15,0:47:05.72,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它的美丽完全超出我的预期\N{\fs13}I'm surprised at how surprised I am at the beauty
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.75,0:47:07.22,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}图像的清晰度也令人惊喜\N{\fs13}and the clarity of these images.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.25,0:47:09.42,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}真是叹为观止\N{\fs13}They are shocking to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.45,0:47:12.92,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}飞船为我们提供了一个非常稳定的平台\N{\fs13}The spacecraft allows us a very steady platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.96,0:47:16.83,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这台机器的指向很稳定\N{\fs13}This machine, you turn it, you point it, and it stays there.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.86,0:47:19.10,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它就像太空中的三脚架\N{\fs13}It's like a tripod in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.13,0:47:22.03,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}无论如何，我想光环科学家们会忙上一阵了\N{\fs13}Anyway, I think ring scientists are gonna have a field day.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.07,0:47:23.47,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}谢谢你\N{\fs13}So thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.47,0:47:27.54,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}哇！\N{\fs13}Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.98,0:47:41.12,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}卡西尼号的到来恰逢其时\N{\fs13}- [Narrator] Cassini's arrival coincided
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.15,0:47:44.76,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}有一段时间土星的光照角度很好，\N{\fs13}with a time when the planet was well lit by sunlight,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.79,0:47:48.19,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}展现了光环的非凡景色\N{\fs13}providing extraordinary views of the rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.63,0:47:53.70,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}土星加上土星环的宽度约为25万英里，\N{\fs13}Saturn, plus the rings, span about a quarter million miles,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.73,0:47:57.10,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这个宽度和地月距离差不多\N{\fs13}and they would fit in between the Earth and its moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.30,0:48:00.77,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}然而，在这个广阔区域中，\N{\fs13}And yet for all of its wide expanse,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.81,0:48:03.88,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}光环本身非常薄，\N{\fs13}the rings themselves are paper thin,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.91,0:48:07.15,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}只有大约10英尺厚\N{\fs13}only about 10 feet thick.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.31,0:48:10.72,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}如果你能收集到所有的环粒子，\N{\fs13}If you could scoop up all the ring particles,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.75,0:48:13.62,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它的质量会比土星的\N{\fs13}there would be less mass than one of Saturn's
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.65,0:48:15.22,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}小卫星Mimas的质量还小\N{\fs13}small moons named Mimas.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.92,0:48:20.23,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}从远处看，\N{\fs13}- [Narrator] From a distance,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.26,0:48:23.09,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}光环散发出一种宁静的感觉，\N{\fs13}the rings cast off a sense of serenity,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.13,0:48:26.93,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但它们既美丽又复杂且混乱\N{\fs13}but they are as complex and chaotic as they are beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.13,0:48:29.87,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因为它们是由无数\N{\fs13}For they are made up of countless numbers
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.90,0:48:33.37,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}不同大小和形状的杂乱无章的物体组成的\N{\fs13}of disorderly objects of different sizes and shapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.58,0:48:40.35,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这是一幅基于雷达观测的模拟图像，\N{\fs13}This is a simulated image based on radar observations,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.38,0:48:43.55,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}依据光环不同区域的颗粒大小\N{\fs13}showing particles sizes found in different regions
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.58,0:48:44.92,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}显示不同的颜色\N{\fs13}of the rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.95,0:48:47.22,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}紫色代表了当前位置\N{\fs13}The color purple represents where there is
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.25,0:48:50.46,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}主要由小于两英寸的物体构成\N{\fs13}a preponderance of objects smaller than two inches.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.49,0:48:54.29,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}绿色区域的颗粒大小约为一英寸\N{\fs13}Particles in green are about an inch in size.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.33,0:48:56.83,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}蓝色条纹的颗粒更小\N{\fs13}The blueish bands are still smaller.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.30,0:49:01.73,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}白色条带是颗粒密集区域\N{\fs13}The white bands are dense regions that radio signals
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.77,0:49:03.27,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}无线电信号无法穿透\N{\fs13}were unable to penetrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.60,0:49:08.81,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}此伪彩色图像突出显示了\N{\fs13}This false color image highlights what can be seen
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.84,0:49:10.01,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}紫外线下可以看到的物体\N{\fs13}in the ultraviolet.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.24,0:49:13.95,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}绿松石色代表水冰\N{\fs13}The turquoise colors represent water ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.98,0:49:17.48,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}红色是一种不同的粒子\N{\fs13}The red colors are a different kind of particle.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.52,0:49:19.62,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}无法确定它的成分，\N{\fs13}Uncertain as to what it might be,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.65,0:49:22.59,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}于是科学家们决定把它命名为尘土\N{\fs13}the scientists decided to name it dirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.79,0:49:25.79,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}卡西尼号也能够测量\N{\fs13}- Cassini was also able to measure
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.82,0:49:28.26,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}环中粒子的温度，\N{\fs13}the temperature of the ring particles,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.29,0:49:31.76,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那些有较多尘土和黑点的光环\N{\fs13}and the rings that had the most dirt or pollution*
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.80,0:49:36.57,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}比明亮的冰环温度稍微高一点\N{\fs13}were slightly warmer than the bright icy rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.60,0:49:38.50,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}尽管主要由\N{\fs13}- [Narrator] And, despite being made of
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.54,0:49:40.71,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}宇宙尘埃和冰组成，\N{\fs13}mostly cosmic dust and ice,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.74,0:49:45.04,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这些圆环中也包含一些像房子一样大的结构\N{\fs13}the rings contained some structures as large as a house.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.08,0:49:48.58,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}科学家们惊奇地发现，\N{\fs13}And as scientists discovered to their astonishment,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.61,0:49:51.35,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}甚至短暂地出现过“山脉”\N{\fs13}even transitory mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.38,0:49:54.49,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}卡西尼号任务有一个独特的时刻\N{\fs13}- There is a unique moment in the Cassini mission
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.52,0:49:56.96,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}那时阳光从环的边缘平行射入，\N{\fs13}where the sun was edge onto the rings,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.99,0:49:59.76,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}这让我们可以看到10英尺厚的圆环上下\N{\fs13}and that allowed us to see anything that would stick up
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.79,0:50:03.93,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}任何凸起的东西\N{\fs13}above or below those 10 feet thick rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.96,0:50:07.97,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}看哪，我们找到了像是山脉的物体\N{\fs13}Then lo and behold, we found what looked like mountains
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.00,0:50:11.30,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在光环上投下巨大的阴影\N{\fs13}casting huge shadows on the rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.34,0:50:13.64,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}结果证明土星的光环\N{\fs13}And it turns out that the rings of Saturn
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.67,0:50:15.67,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}不仅仅是独立的粒子，\N{\fs13}are not like just individual particles,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.71,0:50:18.94,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}还有很多粒子粘在一起\N{\fs13}but a lot of these particles stick together
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.98,0:50:22.58,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}并成长为越来越大的颗粒\N{\fs13}and grow into larger and larger particles.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.61,0:50:25.42,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但这些粒子团是短暂的\N{\fs13}But these clumps of particles are ephemeral.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.45,0:50:27.59,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它们不会持续很长时间\N{\fs13}They don't last for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.62,0:50:32.39,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它们可以分裂，然后重组成新的颗粒\N{\fs13}They can be broken up and then reformed in to new particles.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.56,0:50:39.93,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}土星的卫星和小卫星\N{\fs13}- [Narrator] Saturn's moons and smaller moonlets
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.96,0:50:41.47,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}也影响了光环\N{\fs13}also influenced the rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.00,0:50:47.47,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}即使是轨道上的碎石堆也会摆动\N{\fs13}Even orbiting rubble piles hold a kind of sway.*
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.51,0:50:50.34,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}总之，它们为土星的光环\N{\fs13}Altogether, they help shape the boundaries
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.38,0:50:51.91,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}塑造边界\N{\fs13}of Saturn's rings,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.94,0:50:54.55,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}也聚集了粒子\N{\fs13}herding in particles that might otherwise
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.58,0:50:56.75,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}否则这些颗粒要么坠入土星\N{\fs13}rain down in a torrent on the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.78,0:50:59.38,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}要么逃逸到深空\N{\fs13}or escape into deep space.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.22,0:51:04.46,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}与此同时，一些颗粒\N{\fs13}Meanwhile, particles from some of Saturn's moons
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.49,0:51:06.52,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}从土星的卫星上不断剥离，\N{\fs13}are constantly shedding off,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.56,0:51:11.53,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}帮助保持现有的环或创造出新的环\N{\fs13}helping to preserve existing rings or creating new ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.00,0:51:20.27,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在环内的意外发现\N{\fs13}Among the unexpected discoveries within the rings
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.30,0:51:22.87,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}是这些类似螺旋桨的物体\N{\fs13}were these propeller like objects.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.31,0:51:28.18,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}螺旋桨结构是这些最大的环状粒子团，\N{\fs13}- Propellers are these largest clumps of ring particles,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.21,0:51:30.28,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它们变得足够大，所以它们的重力\N{\fs13}and they get big enough so their gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.32,0:51:33.89,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}想要推开环，打开一个缝隙\N{\fs13}wants to push apart the rings and open up a gap.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.92,0:51:35.35,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}但后来没有足够的重力\N{\fs13}And then there's not quite enough gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.39,0:51:36.59,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}一路打开缺口\N{\fs13}to open it up all the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.62,0:51:38.69,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}你看到这些小螺旋桨了吗\N{\fs13}And so you see these little propellers
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.72,0:51:40.09,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}分布在光环上，\N{\fs13}sprinkled throughout the rings,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.13,0:51:42.23,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}尤其是土星的A环\N{\fs13}especially in Saturn's A ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.46,0:51:47.17,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}有一个可以追溯到旅行者号的谜团\N{\fs13}- [Narrator] A mystery dating back to Voyager
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.20,0:51:51.24,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}是幽灵般出现和消失的辐条\N{\fs13}was the appearing and disappearing of ghostly spokes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.27,0:51:54.14,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}卡西尼号确定了原因\N{\fs13}Cassini determined their cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.17,0:51:57.34,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}静电能使尘埃颗粒上升，\N{\fs13}Electrostatic charges that lift up dust particles,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.38,0:52:00.38,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因此可以在指环之上漂浮一段时间\N{\fs13}where they levitate for a time above the rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.05,0:52:06.88,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}还有两个根本问题\N{\fs13}There remain two fundamental questions
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.92,0:52:09.22,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}没有明确的答案\N{\fs13}lacking definitive answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.25,0:52:12.12,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}首先是光环如何形成\N{\fs13}The first is knowing how the rings came to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.49,0:52:17.00,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}关于光环的许多事情至今仍无法解释\N{\fs13}- So many things about the rings are unexplained even now.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.16,0:52:21.17,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}关于土星光环最初是如何形成的，\N{\fs13}There are a lot of ideas for how Saturn's rings
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.20,0:52:22.83,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}众说纷纭\N{\fs13}initially formed.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.87,0:52:25.97,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}其中一个原因可能是这些环\N{\fs13}One of those is that perhaps the rings formed
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.00,0:52:28.64,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}是在土星形成的时候\N{\fs13}from the material that was left over
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.67,0:52:30.21,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}由剩余的材料组成的\N{\fs13}from when Saturn formed.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.24,0:52:33.44,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}如果这是真的，那么光环是本来就有的，\N{\fs13}So if that's true, then the rings are old,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.48,0:52:35.25,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}和土星本身一样古老\N{\fs13}as old as Saturn itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.68,0:52:40.25,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}其他想法是：假设有一个物体，可能是彗星，\N{\fs13}Other ideas: say perhaps an object may be a comet,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.28,0:52:43.05,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}或者是一颗流星，离土星太近了，\N{\fs13}or a meteor, came in too close to Saturn,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.09,0:52:46.02,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}被土星的引力撕裂，\N{\fs13}was torn apart by Saturn's gravity,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.06,0:52:48.53,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}然后创造了光环\N{\fs13}and then created the rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.56,0:52:51.80,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}或者是一个卫星离土星太近了\N{\fs13}Or perhaps a moon wandered too close to Saturn
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.83,0:52:53.53,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}被土星撕碎\N{\fs13}and was torn apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.56,0:52:57.00,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}因此，光环可能只有\N{\fs13}And so then the rings could be as young as maybe only 10
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.04,0:52:59.27,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}1000万或者一亿年的历史\N{\fs13}or a hundred million years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.54,0:53:04.94,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}除了确定光环的起源，\N{\fs13}- [Narrator] Along with determining the origin of the rings,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.98,0:53:08.78,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}光环的结局也是一个悬而未决的问题\N{\fs13}understanding their fate is also an unanswered question.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.91,0:53:12.48,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}有句格言是：没有什么是永恒的\N{\fs13}But the adage that nothing lasts forever
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.52,0:53:14.89,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}可能也适用于土星环\N{\fs13}likely applies even to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.25,0:53:20.12,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}随着微流星体继续轰击光环，\N{\fs13}- As micro meteoroids continue to bombard the rings,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.16,0:53:23.39,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}一些最里面的粒子落入土星\N{\fs13}and some of the innermost particles fall into Saturn
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.43,0:53:25.56,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}成为它的一部分，\N{\fs13}and actually water* the planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.60,0:53:28.67,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}随着时间的推移，光环颜色会越来越浅\N{\fs13}the rings are getting lighter and lighter with time.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.70,0:53:31.77,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}也许再过几亿年，\N{\fs13}And so perhaps in another few hundred million years,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.80,0:53:34.14,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们所知道的土星环可能已经消失了\N{\fs13}Saturn's rings as we know it might be gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.17,0:53:36.64,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}也许会留下一个狭窄的环\N{\fs13}Maybe we'll be left with narrow rings
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.67,0:53:38.94,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}就像我们在天王星系统看到的那样\N{\fs13}like we see in the Uranus system.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.08,0:53:43.35,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}很久之后的某天，\N{\fs13}- [Narrator] And one day long from now,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.38,0:53:47.59,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}土星光环可能会完全消失\N{\fs13}Saturn's glorious rings might disappear altogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.62,0:53:50.72,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们现在欣赏土星环的理由又多了一个\N{\fs13}One more reason to enjoy them while we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.40,0:54:01.33,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}下次的“JPL与太空时代”节目中，\N{\fs13}Next time on "JPL and the Space Age",
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.37,0:54:05.14,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}“土星上的胜利”的第二部分...\N{\fs13}Part Two of "Triumph at Saturn"...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.17,0:54:09.91,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}卡西尼号安全进入轨道，科学任务占据主导地位，\N{\fs13}With Cassini safely in orbit, science takes center stage,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.38,0:54:14.65,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}以及惠更斯探测器激动人心的\N{\fs13}beginning with the dramatic descent of the Huygens Probe
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.68,0:54:17.88,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}降落到土卫六表面的过程\N{\fs13}to the surface of Saturn's moon Titan.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.05,0:54:20.45,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我们知道泰坦是个很难对付的目标，\N{\fs13}- [Man] We knew Titan was a tough target,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.49,0:54:23.02,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}他恪守自己的秘密\N{\fs13}was going to hold its secrets tightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.05,0:54:25.82,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}所以我们设计了这个任务来揭开它\N{\fs13}And so we designed this mission to hit it
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.86,0:54:27.79,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}尽我们所能\N{\fs13}with everything we've got.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.83,0:54:29.56,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在接下来的几年里，\N{\fs13}- [Narrator] In the years that follow,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.59,0:54:33.26,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}将会取得一个又一个意想不到的发现，\N{\fs13}one unexpected discovery after another will be made,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.30,0:54:35.50,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}为这项国际任务\N{\fs13}earning this international mission
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.53,0:54:37.87,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}赢得来自世界各地的赞誉\N{\fs13}accolades from around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.00,0:54:41.31,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}科学是注重发现，\N{\fs13}- Science is about what is,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.34,0:54:44.84,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而工程学关注实现\N{\fs13}and engineering is about what can BE.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.88,0:54:48.05,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}卡西尼-惠更斯计划\N{\fs13}The Cassini-Huygens program has demonstrated
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.08,0:54:49.58,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}就是两者结合的最佳典范\N{\fs13}the best of both.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.61,0:54:51.88,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}新发现的数量\N{\fs13}The number of your new discoveries
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.92,0:54:54.19,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}简直令人欣喜若狂\N{\fs13}is nothing short of amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.22,0:54:56.52,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我想说卡西尼号的发现\N{\fs13}- [Woman] I would say Cassini's discoveries
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.55,0:55:01.19,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}从根本上改变了我们看待太阳系的方式\N{\fs13}fundamentally altered the way we look at our solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.23,0:55:04.20,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}在一颗行星周围，我们发现了两颗卫星\N{\fs13}Around one planet, we find two moons
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.23,0:55:07.43,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}它们有潜在的宜居条件，\N{\fs13}that could potentially be habitable,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.47,0:55:11.37,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}而且具有支持生命存在的关键成分\N{\fs13}have the key ingredients to support life.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.40,0:55:14.57,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我对土星及其卫星\N{\fs13}- I have more than a passing interest in Saturn
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.61,0:55:16.04,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}热情不减\N{\fs13}and its family of moons.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.07,0:55:20.88,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}卡西尼号发射时，我们只知道18颗卫星\N{\fs13}When Cassini was launched, we knew only 18 moons.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.91,0:55:24.62,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}现在已经发现60个，而且还在增加\N{\fs13}I understand there's now 60 and counting.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.65,0:55:27.52,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}我忍不住要说，\N{\fs13}I can't resist the temptation to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.55,0:55:29.42,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}天哪，竟存在如此之多的卫星\N{\fs13}my God, it's full of moons.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.82,0:55:35.46,new,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}“土星上的胜利”第二部分，且听下回分解\N{\fs13}- [Narrator] "Triumph at Saturn" Part Two, next time.
